Needs scapy, tcpdump .. amoung other things 
these scripts also work on the nokia n900 (need to install tcpdump and scapy on the n900 though)
yeah..

The auto one gets the network you're on from route

the non-auto arp.py needs your network like 192.168.2.0/24

output example:
[root@amd arp]# python2.7 arp.auto.py 
192.168.2.0/24
WARNING: No route found for IPv6 destination :: (no default route?)
192.168.2.1      00:0c:41:xx:xx:xx              Cisco-Li               # Cisco-Linksys
192.168.2.179    00:17:31:xx:xx:xx              AsustekC               # ASUSTek COMPUTER INC.
192.168.2.109    1c:4b:d6:xx:xx:xx              Azurewav               # AzureWave
192.168.2.115    ec:9b:5b:xx:xx:xx              Nokia                  # Nokia Corporation




art.argparse.py now allows for switches :D

usage: arp.argparse.py [-h] [-i IFACE] [-n NETWORK]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help  show this help message and exit
  -i IFACE    force the interface
  -n NETWORK  force the network ex: 192.168.2.0/24

so like:      python2.7 arp.argparse.py -i eth0 -n 10.2.4.0/22 
	will force it to be that interface on that network 
